   abstract = {The increasing failure of antibiotics to combat infections like multi-drug resistant Staphylococcus aureus has renewed interest in a long-forgotten treatment developed over 60 years ago in ex-Soviet Georgia. Tom Parfitt travelled to Tbilisi to witness the revival of bacteriophage therapy.},
